-- Sugar Awaiting Loading at Brazil’s Ports Fell 6.6% in Past Week
-- B y   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 2013-04-11T09:06:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-11/sugar-awaiting-loading-at-brazil-s-ports-fell-6-6-in-past-week.html
The amount of sugar awaiting
loading at ports in top producer  Brazil  fell 6.6 percent over
the past week, according to Williams Servicos Maritimos Ltda.  As many as 764,053 metric tons of sugar were waiting to be
loaded onto ships at the ports of Recife, Maceio, Paranagua and
Santos, the country’s biggest, figures e-mailed yesterday from
the Recife, Brazil-based shipping agency showed. That compares
with about 817,977 tons a week earlier.  Raw sugar for July delivery fell 0.5 percent to 17.79 cents
a pound by 4:40 a.m. on ICE Futures U.S. in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
